# HPUX tickets require a Design Doc

When creating **any** HPUX Epic or Story (including Consult, Make, Explore, Orient, Monitor, Enable):

1. **Create a Google Design Doc** in the same session (follow `hpux-design-doc` skill).
2. **Do not mark ticket creation complete** until the doc exists and is linked.
3. **Always populate Design artifacts** on the ticket with the Google Doc URL before finishing.
4. Add a Jira comment with the design doc link.
5. Prefer Google Doc via Workspace MCP; if auth fails, use Drive upload with `gcloud` (same pattern as prior HPUX docs) — do not leave the ticket without a doc.
6. For Consult / early work, Status may be `In progress` or `Exploration`; still create the doc with problem framing, options, screenshot placeholders, and a stakeholder feedback log.
7. **Pageless required** — after create/import, set Google Docs format to Pageless (`documentFormat.documentMode = PAGELESS` via Docs `batchUpdate`). Never leave new design docs in Pages mode.

## Doc title format

`{Product area} UX — HPUX-{key}` (or descriptive title including the HPUX key)

## Minimum Design artifacts block

```
Design artifacts
- Design doc: https://docs.google.com/document/d/{id}/edit
```

